(He finally gets help.)

270
00:11:12,226 --> 00:11:13,926
So, like this.

271
00:11:14,326 --> 00:11:15,896
Oh, my. I seriously ruined this.

272
00:11:15,996 --> 00:11:18,165
- Great! - Great?

273
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:20,135
Amazing! Are you a professional?

274
00:11:20,136 --> 00:11:21,836
(Yun Nyeong receives a compliment.)

275
00:11:22,566 --> 00:11:25,206
- Good. Cute. - Me too.

276
00:11:26,206 --> 00:11:27,775
- Nice. - Is this professional?

277
00:11:27,776 --> 00:11:29,146
Just a little bit.

278
00:11:30,946 --> 00:11:32,116
This is funny.

279
00:11:32,976 --> 00:11:35,046
I win you over this, too.

280
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:36,516
So,

281
00:11:38,186 --> 00:11:40,425
- can I ask you a question? - Okay.

282
00:11:40,426 --> 00:11:45,056
Are you a couple?

283
00:11:46,656 --> 00:11:51,796
Not yet. But...

284
00:11:52,566 --> 00:11:53,935
- Not yet. - Not yet.

285
00:11:53,936 --> 00:11:55,135
- Not yet? - Not yet?

286
00:11:55,136 --> 00:11:57,006
Do you know what "situationship" means?

287
00:11:58,776 --> 00:12:01,746
What is it?

288
00:12:02,306 --> 00:12:03,476
Yes, well.

289
00:12:03,846 --> 00:12:08,516
Since both of us were wearing a denim jacket,

290
00:12:08,846 --> 00:12:11,256
the employee asked us whether we're a couple.

291
00:12:11,356 --> 00:12:13,556
And Baek Hyun sitting beside me answered,

292
00:12:13,786 --> 00:12:15,356
"Not yet."

293
00:12:17,496 --> 00:12:20,566
I felt good. It felt nice to hear that we looked like a couple.

294
00:12:22,396 --> 00:12:23,396
I'm done.

295
00:12:24,796 --> 00:12:26,595
- Do you want to try this? - No, you go first.

296
00:12:26,596 --> 00:12:28,035
- You tell me. - Shall I?

297
00:12:28,036 --> 00:12:29,235
- Yes. - Say if you'd like this or not?

298
00:12:29,236 --> 00:12:30,236
Yes.

299
00:12:30,976 --> 00:12:33,336
- You'd definitely like this. - It must be so good!

300
00:12:34,006 --> 00:12:36,006
- What's going on? - It should be good.

301
00:12:37,416 --> 00:12:39,115
- It tastes like an apple. - You're lying.

302
00:12:39,116 --> 00:12:40,116
I mean it.

303
00:12:40,786 --> 00:12:41,786
It has an apple taste, right?

304
00:12:43,656 --> 00:12:45,686
This is really good. The sugar...

305
00:12:45,786 --> 00:12:47,086
- An apple taste? - Yes.

306
00:12:47,386 --> 00:12:50,396
I see. It's really good.

307
00:12:50,496 --> 00:12:51,556
- It's good. - Yes.

308
00:12:56,596 --> 00:12:57,965
It's been two days now.

309
00:12:57,966 --> 00:12:59,036
This is so nice.

310
00:12:59,136 --> 00:13:00,136
It's so nice.

311
00:13:00,566 --> 00:13:02,206
I know. It's been two days.

312
00:13:02,306 --> 00:13:04,835
But it feels like I'm having so many new experiences.

313
00:13:04,836 --> 00:13:06,936
Right. We made denim jackets together and all.

314
00:13:08,206 --> 00:13:09,276
I told you this yesterday.

315
00:13:11,316 --> 00:13:13,946
There were so many moments that made my heart flutter.

316
00:13:14,746 --> 00:13:16,116
And what I like the most among what you told me is this.

317
00:13:17,816 --> 00:13:20,856
You said that since this was my first trip to Japan,

318
00:13:21,456 --> 00:13:24,156
you hoped that my first memory of Japan wouldn't be a bad one.

319
00:13:25,856 --> 00:13:28,296
I kept thinking about what you said,

320
00:13:29,196 --> 00:13:31,596
and I definitely wanted to make you happy.

321
00:13:32,666 --> 00:13:35,105
This makes me so happy as well.

322
00:13:35,106 --> 00:13:37,336
I'm happy too.

323
00:13:37,476 --> 00:13:38,636
I will make you happy.

324
00:13:39,206 --> 00:13:42,906
(A moment where Yun Nyeong and Baek Hyun's happiness bloomed wide)

325
00:13:44,516 --> 00:13:48,586
(The third day in Kamakura)

326
00:13:50,286 --> 00:13:53,486
(Yun Nyeong has three dates.)

327
00:13:59,256 --> 00:14:00,866
- Hi! - Hi.

328
00:14:02,326 --> 00:14:04,595
- Did you have fun? - Sure. Did you have fun?

329
00:14:04,596 --> 00:14:06,966
You took all my colors today.

330
00:14:07,066 --> 00:14:08,605
Your outfit looks great. You're dressed so nicely.

331
00:14:08,606 --> 00:14:09,606
Am I?

332
00:14:09,607 --> 00:14:10,635
My hair looks pretty nice today, doesn't it?

333
00:14:10,636 --> 00:14:12,376
- Yes, it looks nice. - It's nicely done, right?

334
00:14:13,206 --> 00:14:14,445
This place is so beautiful.

335
00:14:14,446 --> 00:14:16,045
I heard they filmed something here.

336
00:14:16,046 --> 00:14:17,276
- Really? - Yes.

337
00:14:17,346 --> 00:14:20,145
- You know, "Slam Dunk?" - Right.

338
00:14:20,146 --> 00:14:21,785
- They said so. - Right. I heard that.

339
00:14:21,786 --> 00:14:22,786
(Kamakura is the setting of the Japanese comic "Slam Dunk.")

340
00:14:24,686 --> 00:14:27,656
You looked like you were having a hard time these days.

341
00:14:28,086 --> 00:14:31,056
I wished that you'd feel better while you were here.

342
00:14:33,656 --> 00:14:36,466
I can't really hide what I'm feeling on my face.

343
00:14:36,626 --> 00:14:38,335
- It totally shows. - Really?

344
00:14:38,336 --> 00:14:41,205
My face looks happy when I'm happy, and it's not so great when I'm not.

345
00:14:41,206 --> 00:14:42,406
I'm going to guess how you feel now.

346
00:14:43,206 --> 00:14:44,536
- You look like you're happy. - Of course I am.

347
00:14:44,876 --> 00:14:48,505
I get to come out, relax, and eat something delicious with you.

348
00:14:48,506 --> 00:14:49,646
How could I possibly be in a bad mood?

349
00:14:51,076 --> 00:14:52,746
You're really good with words.

350
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:55,786
I'll cut this for you. I think I need to cut it.

351
00:14:56,586 --> 00:14:58,655
When I'm with other people,

352
00:14:58,656 --> 00:15:00,385
I feel a bit uncomfortable.

353
00:15:00,386 --> 00:15:02,256
- Really? - Yes.

354
00:15:02,486 --> 00:15:04,395
But when I'm with you,

355
00:15:04,396 --> 00:15:06,455
I feel very comfortable.

356
00:15:06,456 --> 00:15:08,196
- You do? - I mean it.

357
00:15:08,326 --> 00:15:10,796
That's why I told you all the time that you're a happy virus.

358
00:15:11,796 --> 00:15:13,135
I mean that in a really good way.

359
00:15:13,136 --> 00:15:14,306
- You do? - Yes.

360
00:15:14,766 --> 00:15:16,566
Right. You said that the most.

361
00:15:16,836 --> 00:15:18,306
(Describe today's date in one sentence.)

362
00:15:18,476 --> 00:15:19,506
Loyalty?

363
00:15:20,676 --> 00:15:21,806
Yes. Loyalty.

364
00:15:22,746 --> 00:15:26,346
We take care of each other.

365
00:15:26,376 --> 00:15:28,416
I feel like that's how we are.

366
00:15:28,946 --> 00:15:31,656
If anything ever gets tough, just reach out anytime.

367
00:15:31,716 --> 00:15:33,416
- We promised. - Right.

368
00:15:33,656 --> 00:15:35,826
I feel most comfortable with you. I really like that.

369
00:15:36,856 --> 00:15:37,896
Bye.

370
00:15:39,656 --> 00:15:41,496
Do it like this. Yes.

371
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:42,666
Bye.

372
00:15:43,796 --> 00:15:44,895
- Bye! - See you later.

373
00:15:44,896 --> 00:15:45,896
Okay.

374
00:15:51,206 --> 00:15:52,206
I like them.

375
00:15:52,207 --> 00:15:54,146
They're like reliable supporters for one another.

376
00:15:54,376 --> 00:15:55,675
Absolutely.

377
00:15:55,676 --> 00:15:57,515
Next,

378
00:15:57,516 --> 00:16:00,515
we gathered the residents' hidden charms.

379
00:16:00,516 --> 00:16:03,215
It'd be so hard to gather all their charms.

380
00:16:03,216 --> 00:16:04,655
- The camera is on for 24 hours. - Right.

381
00:16:04,656 --> 00:16:05,955
I'm curious about this.

382
00:16:05,956 --> 00:16:07,825
Bromance is also important.

383
00:16:07,826 --> 00:16:09,226
I have a feeling that it'll be funny.

384
00:16:09,356 --> 00:16:11,095
(Won Kyu and Yoo Sik, best friends who bridged the generation gap)

385
00:16:11,096 --> 00:16:13,025
This doesn't seem like it'll be easy to organize.

386
00:16:13,026 --> 00:16:14,026
That's what I'm saying.

387
00:16:14,026 --> 00:16:15,026
(Won Kyu and Yoo Sik became roommates on the day they moved in.)

388
00:16:15,027 --> 00:16:16,166
It's quite a lot.

389
00:16:17,196 --> 00:16:19,166
How are you?

390
00:16:19,536 --> 00:16:21,005
Do you feel nervous?

391
00:16:21,006 --> 00:16:22,106
I felt very nervous.

392
00:16:22,506 --> 00:16:24,476
- Did you memorize all their names? - No.

393
00:16:24,636 --> 00:16:27,676
Yun... Yun Nyeong.

394
00:16:28,446 --> 00:16:29,646
Min Kyung.

395
00:16:29,706 --> 00:16:30,846
Yun Yeong?

396
00:16:31,776 --> 00:16:33,446
- Yun is right. - Yes.

397
00:16:33,716 --> 00:16:34,745
But it's Nyeong. Nyeong.

398
00:16:34,746 --> 00:16:35,986
- Nyeong? - It starts with "N."

399
00:16:36,586 --> 00:16:37,816
- It's amazing, right? - Yes.

400
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:42,986
(Awkwardness filled the room.)

401
00:16:43,686 --> 00:16:45,556
I'm most curious about the male residents' age.

402
00:16:46,126 --> 00:16:48,325
Honestly, regarding the female residents...

403
00:16:48,326 --> 00:16:49,666
- Can you guess? - Do you have an idea?

404
00:16:49,866 --> 00:16:52,635
I have a general sense of what their ages might be.

405
00:16:52,636 --> 00:16:53,906
- Really? - Yes, that's right.

406
00:16:53,966 --> 00:16:56,306
I'm not sure about the men. Men are actually...

407
00:16:56,536 --> 00:16:58,276
So you have no idea, and why do you use honorifics to me?

408
00:17:01,946 --> 00:17:04,715
(Yoo Sik's roommate looked older than him, although he wasn't sure.)

409
00:17:04,716 --> 00:17:05,816
This is hilarious.

410
00:17:07,516 --> 00:17:09,415
Gosh. Shall we have a drink?

411
00:17:09,416 --> 00:17:10,616
All right.

412
00:17:10,856 --> 00:17:12,016
Let's have a drink.

413
00:17:12,856 --> 00:17:14,655
(Sighing in frustration)

414
00:17:14,656 --> 00:17:16,586
Do not hold your glass with both hands.

415
00:17:17,626 --> 00:17:19,456
(Yoo Sik's hands naturally come together.)

416
00:17:21,026 --> 00:17:22,066
How come he's talking like that?

417
00:17:23,126 --> 00:17:25,796
Haven't you heard that you resemble Kim Jae Joong?

418
00:17:26,096 --> 00:17:27,505
- I heard that. - He did hear that,

419
00:17:27,506 --> 00:17:29,466
but he said he didn't know what Cassiopeia was.

420
00:17:30,436 --> 00:17:32,576
But I'm not from the Cassiopeia generation either.

421
00:17:32,776 --> 00:17:34,575
I'm more like the NCT generation.

422
00:17:34,576 --> 00:17:36,406
- NCT. - The NCT generation.

423
00:17:37,716 --> 00:17:38,716
How about you, Won Kyu?

424
00:17:40,116 --> 00:17:41,615
Seo Taiji!

425
00:17:41,616 --> 00:17:43,545
What? I'm from the MEOVV generation.

426
00:17:43,546 --> 00:17:44,616
MEOVV?

427
00:17:44,786 --> 00:17:46,416
- MEOVV. - MEOVV?

428
00:17:46,556 --> 00:17:47,755
Yes, I'm from the MEOVV generation.

429
00:17:47,756 --> 00:17:50,456
(Uncle Won Kyu tries to catch up with the Gen Zers.)

430
00:17:50,826 --> 00:17:52,295
Maybe Jewelry was popular in your time.

431
00:17:52,296 --> 00:17:53,896
- "Hands Up." - Hey.

432
00:17:54,596 --> 00:17:55,665
Attention.

433
00:17:55,666 --> 00:17:58,166
(Won Kyu and Yoo Sik showed off brotherly chemistry from the start.)

434
00:17:58,766 --> 00:18:00,966
(A few days later)

435
00:18:01,336 --> 00:18:03,836
I think it's my first time drinking with a man...

436
00:18:04,106 --> 00:18:05,576
who was born in 2000.

437
00:18:05,736 --> 00:18:07,206
- Are you serious? - I'm serious.

438
00:18:07,506 --> 00:18:10,476
It's so fascinating. I don't feel uncomfortable at all.

439
00:18:11,316 --> 00:18:12,875
I'd love it if we remained friends for the rest of our lives.

440
00:18:12,876 --> 00:18:16,886
I know. We'll go through this strange situation together.

441
00:18:17,386 --> 00:18:18,986
It's unusual to share that.

442
00:18:19,256 --> 00:18:20,786
- That's right. - So...

443
00:18:21,126 --> 00:18:23,256
we're bound to become close.

444
00:18:23,956 --> 00:18:25,025
I often thought,

445
00:18:25,026 --> 00:18:29,196
"I really wish he were my friend."

446
00:18:29,396 --> 00:18:30,466
Really?

447
00:18:31,366 --> 00:18:32,865
You might find it arrogant.

448
00:18:32,866 --> 00:18:33,896
No.

449
00:18:34,266 --> 00:18:37,675
You might think, "You are you to say that we're friends?"

450
00:18:37,676 --> 00:18:39,305
Not at all. That's ridiculous.

451
00:18:39,306 --> 00:18:40,335
(Despite the age gap of 7 years, they became friends.)

452
00:18:40,336 --> 00:18:41,406
Not at all.

453
00:18:41,976 --> 00:18:45,316
Seriously, I've said this to Hyeon Ji many times.

454
00:18:45,846 --> 00:18:47,786
I truly enjoyed...

455
00:18:48,646 --> 00:18:49,746
spending time with you.

456
00:18:50,516 --> 00:18:51,556
Same here.

457
00:18:51,756 --> 00:18:52,756
As for me, I'm serious.

458
00:18:53,186 --> 00:18:55,656
Are you saying that I'm not? I mean my words.

459
00:18:57,356 --> 00:18:58,856
Yoo Sik, I usually...

460
00:18:59,996 --> 00:19:03,125
don't like my roommates.

461
00:19:03,126 --> 00:19:05,295
- Really? - I usually can't sleep...

462
00:19:05,296 --> 00:19:06,695
with someone else.

463
00:19:06,696 --> 00:19:07,736
But...

464
00:19:08,536 --> 00:19:10,266
But you even...

465
00:19:10,406 --> 00:19:12,475
- I came back late. - You did that too.

466
00:19:12,476 --> 00:19:13,906
You even woke up early.

467
00:19:15,046 --> 00:19:17,676
I was like, "What's wrong with him?"

468
00:19:18,646 --> 00:19:20,375
But I didn't mind.

469
00:19:20,376 --> 00:19:22,115
I was the worst roommate.

470
00:19:22,116 --> 00:19:23,585
But I didn't mind.

471
00:19:23,586 --> 00:19:24,656
In any case...

472
00:19:26,386 --> 00:19:28,125
Had I been my usual self,

473
00:19:28,126 --> 00:19:29,886
sleeping would've been so freaking uncomfortable.

474
00:19:31,096 --> 00:19:32,595
But things were fine.

475
00:19:32,596 --> 00:19:35,795
You didn't make me uncomfortable. The situation did.

476
00:19:35,796 --> 00:19:37,995
I couldn't sleep even when I was lying down.

477
00:19:37,996 --> 00:19:39,466
That was what made me uncomfortable,

478
00:19:40,136 --> 00:19:41,506
not you coming back.

479
00:19:43,136 --> 00:19:46,106
I want to thank Yoo Sik...

480
00:19:46,576 --> 00:19:49,676
for leading me outside when I wasn't doing anything.

481
00:19:50,106 --> 00:19:52,646
Despite being seven years younger than me,

482
00:19:52,976 --> 00:19:55,916
Yoo Sik didn't get uneasy around me after our ages got revealed.

483
00:19:57,016 --> 00:19:59,786
I want to thank him for treating me the same.

484
00:19:59,916 --> 00:20:02,686
I like Won Kyu.

485
00:20:03,486 --> 00:20:05,196
I call him "Big brother..."

486
00:20:06,056 --> 00:20:08,366
very seldom...

487
00:20:08,526 --> 00:20:09,866
because there's a nickname.

488
00:20:10,126 --> 00:20:12,696
I usually call him "Kyu."

489
00:20:13,836 --> 00:20:16,466
Won Kyu is such a nice person.

490
00:20:18,506 --> 00:20:20,435
- We'll go downstairs for a moment. - Okay.

491
00:20:20,436 --> 00:20:21,746
(Baek Hyun and Yoo Sik, Why we feel a pull toward each other)

492
00:20:22,106 --> 00:20:23,975
(The day of moving in)

493
00:20:23,976 --> 00:20:25,816
What? All the luggage is here.

494
00:20:26,816 --> 00:20:28,185
I don't know whose suitcases these are.

495
00:20:28,186 --> 00:20:29,885
Shall we move all of them?

496
00:20:29,886 --> 00:20:31,555
Shall I push them inside?

497
00:20:31,556 --> 00:20:32,916
- Okay. - Then you can move them inside.

498
00:20:33,686 --> 00:20:36,456
I think these belong to the same person.

499
00:20:37,326 --> 00:20:38,356
These two.

500
00:20:38,556 --> 00:20:39,626
They belong to the same person?

501
00:20:40,096 --> 00:20:42,266
(When Baek Hyun moved the suitcases from the outside to the inside,)

502
00:20:43,696 --> 00:20:47,506
(Yoo Sik delivered them to the doors.)

503
00:20:50,036 --> 00:20:52,035
They're heavy, right? Oh, no.

504
00:20:52,036 --> 00:20:53,406
(My goodness!)

505
00:20:59,776 --> 00:21:01,315
- Thank you. - Is this all?

506
00:21:01,316 --> 00:21:02,386
Yes.

507
00:21:04,116 --> 00:21:05,156
Thank you.

508
00:21:08,486 --> 00:21:13,656
(You moved the suitcases with Baek Hyun.)

509
00:21:14,126 --> 00:21:15,126
Baek Hyun?

510
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:20,466
I thought, "This man is dependable."

511
00:21:22,466 --> 00:21:24,676
He was just cool.

512
00:21:27,806 --> 00:21:28,806
Yoo Sik?

513
00:21:30,206 --> 00:21:32,516
Among men,

514
00:21:33,076 --> 00:21:35,046
he became my friend first.

515
00:21:36,016 --> 00:21:37,345
I think we get along.

516
00:21:37,346 --> 00:21:39,016
His personality is very cheerful and nice.

517
00:21:40,786 --> 00:21:44,596
(The night we met for the first time)

518
00:21:47,056 --> 00:21:48,596
(Glancing over)

519
00:21:56,236 --> 00:21:58,336
- Do you want to wear an apron? - Me?

520
00:22:01,976 --> 00:22:03,605
I felt like kimchi would get on his clothes.

521
00:22:03,606 --> 00:22:06,675
Kimchi kept getting pushed forward.

522
00:22:06,676 --> 00:22:07,686
So I...

523
00:22:07,986 --> 00:22:09,186
Thank you.

524
00:22:10,646 --> 00:22:12,216
I put an apron on him.

525
00:22:15,856 --> 00:22:17,696
- What? - What?

526
00:22:18,496 --> 00:22:19,726
This is insane.

527
00:22:21,626 --> 00:22:22,726
Thank you.

528
00:22:23,626 --> 00:22:27,606
That was when I began going, "What's this?"

529
00:22:29,366 --> 00:22:32,976
(Baek Hyun was the first one to take a step closer.)

530
00:22:36,246 --> 00:22:37,276
What? No.

531
00:22:37,776 --> 00:22:38,776
Baek Hyun.

532
00:22:39,316 --> 00:22:40,316
Yes.

533
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:42,015
I like someone with big eyes.

534
00:22:42,016 --> 00:22:43,746
